{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Anuchin Glacier | other_name = | photo = Antarctica, Norway territorial claim (Queen Maud Land, 2015).svg | photo_alt = | photo_caption = Location of Queen Maud Land in Antarctica | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Anuchin Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = | location = [[Queen Maud Land]] | coordinates = {{coord|71|17|S|13|31|E|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = | width = | thickness = unknown | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Lake Untersee]] | status = unknown | embedded = }}
'''Anuchin Glacier''' ({{Coord|71|17|S|13|31|E|display=inline,title}}) is a [[glacier]] draining southward to [[Lake Unter-See]] in the northern part of the [[Gruber Mountains]], [[Queen Maud Land]]. It was discovered, and plotted from air photos, by the [[Third German Antarctic Expedition]], 1938&ndash;39. It was mapped from air photos and from surveys by the [[Sixth Norwegian Antarctic Expedition]], 1956&ndash;60, and remapped by the [[Soviet Antarctic Expedition]], 1960&ndash;61, and named after [[Dmitry Nikolayevich Anuchin]], Soviet geographer.
