{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Bogen Glacier | other_name = | photo = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | map = United Kingdom South Georgia | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Bogen Glacier in South Georgia | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = | location = [[South Georgia Island|South Georgia]] | coordinates = {{coord|54|48|S|35|56|W|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = | width = | thickness = unknown | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = | status = retreat | embedded = }}
'''Bogen Glacier''' ({{Coord|54|48|S|35|56|W|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a small [[glacier]] on the north side of [[Drygalski Fjord]] between [[Trendall Crag]] and [[Hamilton Bay]], at the southeast end of [[South Georgia Island|South Georgia]]. It was named by the [[UK Antarctic Place-Names Committee]] in 1979 after [[Arne Bogen]], Norwegian sealer working in South Georgia after 1950; Master of the sealing vessel ''Albatross'' and Station Foreman, [[Grytviken]].
