The '''Handbook of Australian Soils''' is a [[soil classification|soil classification system]] developed for Australian soils. The first edition was published in 1968<ref>{{cite book |last1=Stace |first1=H.C.T. |last2=Hubble |first2=G.D. |last3=Brewer |first3=R. |last4=Northcote |first4=K.H. |last5=Sleeman |first5=J.R. |last6=Mulcahy |first6=M.J. |last7=Hallsworth |first7=E.G. |year=1968 |title=A Handbook of Australian Soils |publisher=Rellim Technical Publications |location=Glenside, South Australia}}</ref> and is based on the great soil group classification system published by [[James Arthur Prescott|J. A. Prescott]] in 1931.<ref>{{cite book |last=Prescott |first=James A. |authorlink=James Arthur Prescott |year=1931 |title=The soils of Australia in relation to vegetation and climate |publisher=Australian Council of Scientific and Industrial Research |series=Bulletin No. 52}}</ref> It has since been superseded by the [[Australian Soil Classification]].

